Confidence Petroleum Climbs Most in a Week on Bottling Orders

-- B y   A m e y a   K a r v e
-- 
2011-03-01T10:37:49Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-01/confidence-petroleum-climbs-most-in-a-week-on-bottling-orders.html
Confidence Petroleum  India  Ltd.
jumped the most in a week in Mumbai trading after getting orders
from Bharat Petroleum Corp. and Hindustan Petroleum Corp. to
bottle liquefied petroleum gas.  Shares of the manufacturer of LPG bottles increased 4
percent at 18.3 rupees as of the 3:30 p.m. local time close.  Confidence Petroleum didn’t state the details of the
orders, from India’s second and third-largest state-run refiners
respectively, in its statement to the stock exchange today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ameya Karve in Mumbai 
 akarve@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Darren Boey at 
 dboey@bloomberg.net . 